Project Overview

This project is a Task Progress Tracker developed using Java Swing.
It allows users to add tasks, track progress, mark tasks as completed, and delete tasks using a graphical user interface.

The system simulates a real-world task management tool where tasks are dynamically updated and progress is tracked using threads.

Objectives
Understand Java GUI development using Swing
Implement task tracking system
Use threads for progress updates
Manage tasks using collections
Build an interactive application

Tools & Technologies
Java
JDK 8 or above
Swing (GUI)
VS Code / Eclipse / IntelliJ

Modules Used
javax.swing → for GUI components
java.awt → for layout and design
java.util.ArrayList → for storing tasks
java.util.HashMap → for storing task progress

Project Description
The application allows users to manage tasks with the following features:
Add new tasks
Track progress (0% to 100%)
Mark tasks as completed
Delete tasks

Each task’s progress is updated using threads, simulating real-time task execution.

The GUI provides an easy-to-use interface with buttons and task lists.


Key Concepts Used
Java Swing (GUI)
Multithreading
ArrayList
HashMap
Event Handling

Algorithm
Start the program
Open GUI window
Enter task name
Click Add Task

Select a task
Click Start Progress
Update progress using thread

Click Mark Completed
Click Delete Task if needed

Repeat until exit

Features
GUI-based application
Add and manage tasks
Real-time progress tracking
Multithreading implementation
Mark tasks as completed
